riverstone holdings llc announced on march  that they have committed up to  billion as a part of a new joint venture to develop a global platform of utilityscale solar photovoltaic projects together these firms have provided  million of capital over five years to invest in pv solar projects around the world this jointly owned entity is known as aes solar they seek to be the leading global developer and operator of utilityscale solar installations that will be connected to power grids that supply and businesses these installations consist of land based solar pv panels that capture sunlight and convert it to electricity in order to feed the power grid referencesedit  p f lapeyre jrand miss hodgesto wed in march nytimescom  retrieved    did goldman goose oil forbes april    archived copy archived from the original on july   retrieved october     mouawad jad kinder morgan agrees to an improved buyout offer led by its chairman the new york times august    centopani paul  buyouts archive  pe hub buyoutsnewscom retrieved    archived copy archived from the original on september   retrieved august     riverstone raises  billion for energy fund reuters  june  retrieved  august    extol energy formed to pursue power investment opportunities with riverstone holdings  april  retrieved  august    pay to play scandal in ny nabs another investment firm abc  june  retrieved  august    green initiative task force pdf retrieved  june    riverstone aes partner for b solar projects venture reliableplantcom retrieved   other sourcesedit williams to sell control of energy unit for  billion the new york times tuesday april   carlyle riverstone power up with b for two funds firms add more public pensions to lp base the new york times private equity week april   lord brownes renewable career business week october   retrieved from httpsenwikipediaorgwindexphptitleriverstoneholdingsoldid categories private equity firms of the united statesenergy companies of the united statespower companies of